    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="226"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d226">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                        Polish Prime Minister</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mikołajczyk</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d226fn1">Sent by the White House Map Room at
                        Washington to the United States Naval Attaché, London, via Navy channels,
                        upon instructions from Roosevelt to Hopkins contained in telegram No. <gloss
                            target="#t_MRin1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">MR–in</hi>
                        </gloss>–144 of September 11, 1944. The Map Room considered that this
                        message replied to the two messages from Mikołajczyk printed <hi
                            rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_204">pp. 204</ref>, <ref
                            target="#pg_205">205</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quebec</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-11">11 September
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_WH1">WH</gloss> 61. For Prime Minister Mikołajczyk of Poland
                    from President Roosevelt.</p>
                <p>I want to assure you that we are taking every possible step to bring Allied
                    assistance as speedily as possible to the Warsaw garrison. I realize fully the
                    urgent importance of this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
